{"slug": "thaumaturge", "root": "thaumaturge", "category": "profession", "gloss": "a wonder-worker", "definition": "A thaumaturge is a worker of wonders — one who produces marvels and miracles, whether by holiness or by art. The word describes an effect rather than a method: where a conjurer names his means (summoning spirits) and a diviner his end (hidden knowledge), the thaumaturge is known simply by the astonishing result. It was applied first to miracle-working saints, then to magicians.", "history": "The word is Greek *thaumatourgos*, 'wonder-worker' (*thauma*, 'wonder,' plus *ergon*, 'work') — the same *ergon* hidden in *theurgy* and *energy*. It attached first to holy marvel-workers: Byzantine hagiography celebrates figures like St. Theodore of Sykeon as thaumaturges. The turn was its migration from sanctity into the suspect. By the Renaissance, John Dee, as Håkansson shows, could dismiss 'thaumaturgy' or mere 'wonder-working' as illicit ritual that did not draw its power from true divinity — even while listing thaumaturgy among the mathematical arts. The word lands ambivalent, poised between the saint's miracle and the conjurer's trick.", "def_sources": [{"label": "Håkansson, Seeing the Word: John Dee and Renaissance Occultism", "where": "Renaissance magic (PDF)"}, {"label": "Meyer & Mirecki, Magic and Ritual in the Ancient World", "where": "Renaissance magic (PDF)"}, {"label": "Etymonline, s.v. thaumaturgy (Greek thaumatourgos)", "where": "Etymology reference"}], "is_keyword": false, "etymology": {"lang": "Greek", "origin": "Greek thaumatourgos 'wonder-worker' (thauma 'wonder' + ergon 'work')", "first": "1715", "note": "Applied first to miracle-working saints, then to conjurers. Same ergon ('work') that hides in theurgy and energy.", "hook": "Saints as the original wonder-workers."}, "essay": null, "sources": ["Etymonline (Douglas Harper)", "Wiktionary", "classical lexica (Lewis & Short, LSJ, Bosworth–Toller)", "Ted's historical-magic DBs (WitchcraftStudiesDB, AgrippaDOP, MedievalMagicDB)"], "stats": {"flavor_total": 3, "oracle_total": 0, "in_flavor_cards": 3, "in_oracle_cards": 0, "name_match_count": 5, "by_variant": {"thaumaturges": 2, "thaumaturge": 1}, "first_year": 1997, "colors": {"R": 2, "U": 4, "G": 1, "C": 1}, "by_year": {"1997": 1, "2007": 1, "2014": 2, "2017": 1, "2020": 2}}, "cards": [{"id": "70d2f5f7-f727-48e1-9532-8d365b1c1ae5", "name": "Battlefield Thaumaturge", "set": "JOU", "type_line": "Creature — Human Wizard", "rarity": "rare", "colors": ["U"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/4/6/467ffc93-b107-457c-af04-a1b682a4b886.jpg?1782713432", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/4/6/467ffc93-b107-457c-af04-a1b682a4b886.jpg?1782713432", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/jou/31/battlefield-thaumaturge?utm_source=api", "local": "img/thaumaturge/70d2f5f7-f727-48e1-9532-8d365b1c1ae5.jpg"}, {"id": "019d0013-52fd-4261-9cc8-7efcee5a4616", "name": "Dwarven Thaumaturgist", "set": "WTH", "type_line": "Creature — Dwarf Shaman", "rarity": "rare", "colors": ["R"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/8/e/8e68aa29-9f38-48a2-b00a-39aef9d91f6d.jpg?1782721038", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/8/e/8e68aa29-9f38-48a2-b00a-39aef9d91f6d.jpg?1782721038", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/wth/98/dwarven-thaumaturgist?utm_source=api", "local": "img/thaumaturge/019d0013-52fd-4261-9cc8-7efcee5a4616.jpg"}, {"id": "148331cc-24de-481f-9131-c3089d1ff7ce", "name": "Protean Thaumaturge", "set": "THB", "type_line": "Creature — Human Wizard", "rarity": "rare", "colors": ["U"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/7/4/749bfd81-c61b-4901-8efb-72611fd08244.jpg?1782707624", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/7/4/749bfd81-c61b-4901-8efb-72611fd08244.jpg?1782707624", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/thb/60/protean-thaumaturge?utm_source=api", "local": "img/thaumaturge/148331cc-24de-481f-9131-c3089d1ff7ce.jpg"}, {"i